  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220&deg;C/ 200&deg;C (fan)/ 425&deg;F/ Gas 7</p>\r\n<p>Boil a kettle</p>\r\n<p>Peel and finely slice the <strong>brown onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1298.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1298.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1298.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1298.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1298.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a large knob of <strong>butter</strong> over a medium-low heat&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Once melted, add the<strong>&nbsp;sliced onion&nbsp;</strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 6-8 min or until softened&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1298.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1298.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1298.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1298.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1298.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>macaroni</strong> to&nbsp;a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a large pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p>\r\n<p>Cook the <strong>macaroni</strong> for 5 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p>\r\n<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>Grate the <strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1298.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1298.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1298.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1298.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1298.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the <strong>macaroni</strong> has had 5 min, add the <strong>Tenderstem broccoli</strong> and cook for 2 min further until everything's tender</p>\r\n<p>Once done, drain the <strong>macaroni</strong> and <strong>broccoli</strong>, reserving 300ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span> of the <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1298.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1298.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1298.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1298.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1298.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the <strong>onion</strong>&nbsp;has softened, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>drained pasta</strong> and <strong>broccoli</strong> to the pan with the <strong>cr&egrave;me fra&icirc;che</strong>&nbsp;and a generous pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and <strong>pepper&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>basil nut</strong>&nbsp;<strong>pesto pots</strong>, <strong>grated cheddar</strong> and 200ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[350ml]</span> of the<strong> starchy pasta water</strong> and give everything a good old mix up&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1298.-step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1298.-step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1298.-step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1298.-step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1298.-step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>baby leaf&nbsp;</strong><strong>spinach</strong> and cook for 1 min further, stirring until <span class=\"text-highlight\">it's</span> wilted</p>\r\n<p>Tip: add a splash more pasta water if the sauce is looking a bit dry &ndash; remember it will thicken in the oven!&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1298.-step-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1298.-step-6-x400.jpg",
